How can I not believe it?

264
00:23:37,760 --> 00:23:40,400
Then I hope you're ready to go to court

265
00:23:41,040 --> 00:23:43,400
because that reporter's already named you.

266
00:23:45,080 --> 00:23:47,120
As for anyone else involved,

267
00:23:47,640 --> 00:23:49,640
Mr. Thee won't let you get off easy.

268
00:23:55,760 --> 00:23:57,040
You think I'm scared?

269
00:23:58,000 --> 00:23:59,920
You know who my father is.

270
00:24:00,800 --> 00:24:01,800
Of course I do.

271
00:24:02,320 --> 00:24:04,280
Everybody knows your father.

272
00:24:05,920 --> 00:24:08,080
But if a minister's daughter
ends up in court

273
00:24:08,680 --> 00:24:10,720
for something this stupid,

274
00:24:10,800 --> 00:24:12,640
that should be a big scandal, right?

275
00:24:13,760 --> 00:24:16,960
I heard your father's aiming
for a Grade A ministry this year too.

276
00:24:19,680 --> 00:24:21,280
You dare threaten me?

277
00:24:22,080 --> 00:24:24,800
I wasn't. I just wanted to inform you.

278
00:24:27,200 --> 00:24:28,840
You'd better be ready too.

279
00:24:28,920 --> 00:24:31,200
After all, you took the picture.

280
00:24:48,560 --> 00:24:49,600
Here.

281
00:24:57,800 --> 00:24:58,880
Kongkwan,

282
00:25:00,480 --> 00:25:02,120
are you still upset with me?

283
00:25:03,680 --> 00:25:06,840
Gino said you're going to remarry.

284
00:25:06,920 --> 00:25:08,640
It's a lie, right?

285
00:25:10,560 --> 00:25:11,800
It is.

286
00:25:12,680 --> 00:25:15,120
You see how I work every day.

287
00:25:15,200 --> 00:25:16,800
So who would I marry?

288
00:25:18,040 --> 00:25:20,160
That's what I thought too.

289
00:25:20,960 --> 00:25:23,000
And do you still love Daddy?

290
00:25:25,200 --> 00:25:28,920
Poonpun told me his mom and dad

291
00:25:29,000 --> 00:25:30,520
don't love each other anymore.

292
00:25:31,280 --> 00:25:33,760
{\an8}They always fight
whenever they're together,

293
00:25:33,840 --> 00:25:38,040
and they aren't together anymore,
just like you and Daddy.

294
00:25:39,640 --> 00:25:41,480
And if that's the case for me,

295
00:25:42,280 --> 00:25:43,640
would it make you sad?

296
00:25:43,720 --> 00:25:44,960
No, it wouldn't.

297
00:25:45,040 --> 00:25:47,400
I'll still have you and Grandma.

298
00:25:49,160 --> 00:25:55,520
But you have to promise me
you won't love anyone other than me.

299
00:25:59,760 --> 00:26:03,160
I promise I'll love you only.

300
00:26:04,520 --> 00:26:05,480
Come here.

301
00:26:25,000 --> 00:26:26,240
Wanna eat something else?

302
00:26:26,880 --> 00:26:27,880
Some french fries?

303
00:26:28,760 --> 00:26:29,880
French fries it is.

304
00:26:31,760 --> 00:26:33,360
Here you go.

305
00:26:33,960 --> 00:26:36,600
Want some sauce? You want the sauce too?

306
00:26:36,680 --> 00:26:37,520
‪Come on.

307
00:26:37,600 --> 00:26:39,400
Good job!

308
00:26:39,920 --> 00:26:41,160
Whose daughter is this?

309
00:26:42,000 --> 00:26:42,920
Who's your mommy?

310
00:26:52,240 --> 00:26:53,680
How do you feel about Mook?

311
00:26:55,920 --> 00:26:58,320
What about you? How do you feel about her?

312
00:27:01,760 --> 00:27:04,680
Mook and I are good friends.

313
00:27:04,760 --> 00:27:06,480
We talk about everything,

314
00:27:07,160 --> 00:27:08,360
and we get each other,

315
00:27:09,760 --> 00:27:13,200
probably because we have a lot in common.

316
00:27:14,320 --> 00:27:16,520
Your families, for one thing.

317
00:27:20,560 --> 00:27:22,040
You must already know all about me.

318
00:27:33,000 --> 00:27:37,080
Mook and I may have nothing in common,

319
00:27:38,600 --> 00:27:42,200
but I insist that
I do have feelings for her

320
00:27:43,280 --> 00:27:45,880
like a man likes a woman.

321
00:27:49,120 --> 00:27:51,080
How well do you think you know her?

322
00:27:51,720 --> 00:27:52,840
I'm well aware

323
00:27:54,240 --> 00:27:55,640
that she's still afraid of love

324
00:27:56,400 --> 00:27:57,840
and too scared to start over.

325
00:27:58,440 --> 00:28:02,280
So how can you be sure
you won't hurt her just like before?

326
00:28:04,120 --> 00:28:06,320
So this is why you're still confused

327
00:28:07,800 --> 00:28:09,120
about your relationship with Mook.

328
00:28:10,280 --> 00:28:13,600
You're afraid of getting hurt again too.

329
00:28:16,280 --> 00:28:17,760
But for me,

330
00:28:18,600 --> 00:28:20,960
when I'm serious about something,

331
00:28:21,960 --> 00:28:23,120
I won't be afraid,

332
00:28:24,240 --> 00:28:27,320
and I'll make sure I win.

333
00:28:29,600 --> 00:28:32,880
I'll show Mook that love isn't scary.

334
00:28:42,320 --> 00:28:43,840
Don't worry,

335
00:28:45,120 --> 00:28:46,120
I'm serious about Mook.

336
00:28:47,560 --> 00:28:49,400
So if you also like her

337
00:28:50,080 --> 00:28:52,920
and wish to compete with me,
then by all means.

338
00:28:54,360 --> 00:28:55,560
But if not,

339
00:28:56,400 --> 00:28:57,880
get out of my way.

340
00:28:59,960 --> 00:29:02,040
As for Ms. Primprao

341
00:29:02,760 --> 00:29:04,720
being involved with that reporter,

342
00:29:05,560 --> 00:29:06,880
I'll let it slide.

343
00:29:07,400 --> 00:29:09,720
But you must tell her
to apologize to Mook.

344
00:29:22,280 --> 00:29:24,480
You want me to apologize to Mook?

345
00:29:24,560 --> 00:29:25,760
No way!

346
00:29:26,280 --> 00:29:28,800
You made both her and my company look bad.

347
00:29:28,880 --> 00:29:30,760
You're lucky Mr. Thee's not suing you.

348
00:29:32,160 --> 00:29:35,480
I already told you
I'd make her life miserable.

349
00:29:36,000 --> 00:29:37,480
My plan just went a little wrong,

350
00:29:37,560 --> 00:29:39,360
so that single mom
hit the jackpot instead.

351
00:29:39,440 --> 00:29:41,360
You have to apologize to her,
no matter what.

352
00:29:41,440 --> 00:29:43,160
You have no right to ruin anyone's life.

353
00:29:43,880 --> 00:29:46,000
But she has the right
to destroy my family?

354
00:29:46,080 --> 00:29:48,000
How many times have I told you

355
00:29:48,080 --> 00:29:51,160
Mook has nothing to do
with our family falling apart?

356
00:29:51,240 --> 00:29:53,440
We're the ones who ruined
our own relationship.

357
00:29:53,520 --> 00:29:54,960
Don't you get it, Prao?

358
00:29:55,480 --> 00:29:57,120
We're the ones to blame!

359
00:30:00,240 --> 00:30:02,120
We don't love each other anymore.

360
00:30:02,800 --> 00:30:04,720
I'm tired of putting up with this.

361
00:30:04,800 --> 00:30:06,640
I can't move forward,
but I can't fall back.

362
00:30:06,720 --> 00:30:08,080
I think it's time to stop.

363
00:30:08,160 --> 00:30:11,440
We should stop fighting
and just end things already.

364
00:30:16,680 --> 00:30:18,320
Let's get a divorce, Prao.

365
00:30:31,680 --> 00:30:35,440
You're just a coward
who won't admit the truth!

366
00:30:36,640 --> 00:30:38,320
You just like Mook better than me.

367
00:30:38,400 --> 00:30:40,560
This wouldn't have happened
if it weren't for her!

368
00:30:40,640 --> 00:30:42,200
It's happened for a while now, Prao.

369
00:30:42,280 --> 00:30:44,480
Even before I met Mook!

370
00:30:49,600 --> 00:30:51,240
Just accept the truth, Prao.

371
00:30:52,760 --> 00:30:54,800
We can't go on any further.

372
00:31:43,000 --> 00:31:45,280
I'll get these files to Mr. Thee.

373
00:31:45,360 --> 00:31:47,760
Can you set up a meeting
with the department heads?

374
00:31:47,840 --> 00:31:49,040
Of course.

375
00:32:01,160 --> 00:32:02,320
Mrs. Anna?

376
00:32:02,400 --> 00:32:05,280
{\an8}MRS. ANNA

377
00:32:09,600 --> 00:32:12,640
As for the reception,
we haven't really been affected.

378
00:32:12,720 --> 00:32:14,640
We've still had quite a few customers

379
00:32:14,720 --> 00:32:17,200
calling us or coming
to the front desk to inquire

380
00:32:17,280 --> 00:32:19,880
about the special campaign
you plan to promote.

381
00:32:21,440 --> 00:32:22,280
That's good.

382
00:32:22,800 --> 00:32:25,320
I think, if we capitalize on this crisis,

383
00:32:25,400 --> 00:32:27,480
it'll be good for our hotel.

384
00:32:27,560 --> 00:32:28,440
Yes.

385
00:32:29,880 --> 00:32:31,160
- Mr. Pitak,
- Yes?

386
00:32:31,240 --> 00:32:33,760
please tell Ms. Mook to summarize
this year's marketing plan

387
00:32:33,840 --> 00:32:35,640
for servicing tourists.

388
00:32:36,640 --> 00:32:37,800
Sure, Mr. Thee.

389
00:32:39,200 --> 00:32:40,720
I want to scale our brand.

390
00:32:41,240 --> 00:32:42,560
Apart from the hotel,

391
00:32:43,160 --> 00:32:45,760
I want us to offer package tours
as another option

392
00:32:45,840 --> 00:32:47,400
for our customers.

393
00:32:55,160 --> 00:32:56,360
Mr. Pitak,

394
00:32:56,920 --> 00:32:58,160
are you alright?

395
00:32:58,240 --> 00:32:59,280
You don't look too good.

396
00:33:08,320 --> 00:33:09,360
Mom.

397
00:33:16,360 --> 00:33:17,240
John?

398
00:33:18,280 --> 00:33:19,240
John.

399
00:33:22,080 --> 00:33:23,120
John!

400
00:34:08,880 --> 00:34:11,080
Why didn't you tell me you were coming?

401
00:34:11,679 --> 00:34:13,400
I would've picked you up at the airport.

402
00:34:15,600 --> 00:34:17,719
I just wanted to check on you,

403
00:34:17,800 --> 00:34:19,800
see if you're hiding any secrets from me.

404
00:34:34,320 --> 00:34:35,679
I've seen the news.

405
00:34:36,480 --> 00:34:39,320
You were just signing a contract
with a supplier.

406
00:34:39,400 --> 00:34:41,000
What's with all the fuss?

407
00:34:41,800 --> 00:34:43,920
It was only for damage control.

408
00:34:44,560 --> 00:34:47,560
That day, one of the reporters
tried to sabotage the event.

409
00:34:47,639 --> 00:34:51,480
You mean the news
that you're dating that woman

410
00:34:51,560 --> 00:34:53,360
is false?

411
00:34:57,440 --> 00:34:58,720
You know,

412
00:34:59,320 --> 00:35:01,800
I don't want to see you
in this kind of news again.

413
00:35:03,520 --> 00:35:05,160
Whatever you do,

414
00:35:05,240 --> 00:35:07,240
please think about Bell.

415
00:35:11,640 --> 00:35:12,480
‪One more thing.

416
00:35:13,680 --> 00:35:15,480
When there's this kind of news,

417
00:35:16,160 --> 00:35:19,240
many of our stockholders will get upset

418
00:35:19,840 --> 00:35:21,480
because it looks unprofessional

419
00:35:22,000 --> 00:35:25,520
if you get involved
with someone you've hired.

420
00:35:26,920 --> 00:35:29,680
Should we just change our supplier
to get it over with?

421
00:35:29,760 --> 00:35:30,800
I'm afraid we can't.

422
00:35:31,640 --> 00:35:34,160
I judged them fairly in the contest.

423
00:35:37,720 --> 00:35:39,680
I chose A Round Trip Travel

424
00:35:39,760 --> 00:35:42,960
because I saw that they're suitable.

425
00:35:43,560 --> 00:35:44,560
They're capable.

426
00:35:45,160 --> 00:35:47,720
They'll work well as our partner.

427
00:35:50,000 --> 00:35:51,840
Or do you not believe in my judgment?

428
00:35:52,440 --> 00:35:54,480
But the news that got out

429
00:35:54,560 --> 00:35:58,160
makes our stockholders
see us as unprofessional.

430
00:36:04,160 --> 00:36:06,800
Then, I'll prove it to you.

431
00:36:08,840 --> 00:36:11,840
I'll make sure we reach our target
in the first quarter.

432
00:36:12,560 --> 00:36:14,080
Surely the numbers

433
00:36:14,160 --> 00:36:16,800
can reassure our stockholders, right?

434
00:36:19,360 --> 00:36:20,400
Fine.

435
00:36:21,080 --> 00:36:24,360
Well, I'm curious to see if that company

436
00:36:24,440 --> 00:36:27,360
is any good, like you said.

437
00:36:35,440 --> 00:36:38,320
Ma'am, how long do you plan to stay here?

438
00:36:38,400 --> 00:36:40,360
I'll arrange your accommodation.

439
00:36:43,520 --> 00:36:45,440
No need. I'm flying back right away.

440
00:36:45,960 --> 00:36:47,640
Have the driver take me to the airport.

441
00:36:56,440 --> 00:36:59,200
I hope you won't disappoint me, Thee.

442
00:37:21,280 --> 00:37:23,720
I want to know
everything about that woman.

443
00:37:24,640 --> 00:37:25,960
What was her name again?

444
00:37:26,040 --> 00:37:27,280
It's Ms. Mook, ma'am.

445
00:37:27,960 --> 00:37:30,200
Keep me updated on every situation.

446
00:37:30,720 --> 00:37:32,000
Do you understand, Pitak?

447
00:37:32,640 --> 00:37:34,240
Yes, Mrs. Anna.

448
00:37:36,160 --> 00:37:38,800
You know, my boss chewed me out

449
00:37:38,880 --> 00:37:40,880
for not fact-checking first.

450
00:37:41,680 --> 00:37:44,320
What if we caught him lying?

451
00:37:44,920 --> 00:37:48,680
What if those two weren't really together,

452
00:37:49,200 --> 00:37:51,960
but only told a lie
to handle the situation?

453
00:37:52,040 --> 00:37:55,840
If that's the case, Mr. Thee
would be seen as a fraud

454
00:37:56,400 --> 00:37:58,840
who lied to spread fake news
and deceive people.

455
00:38:07,040 --> 00:38:08,240
{\an8}Boss.

456
00:38:08,320 --> 00:38:11,680
If the performance evaluation needs
exact numbers, can we really do it?

457
00:38:12,280 --> 00:38:16,480
These days, people like to travel
on their own without a travel agency.

458
00:38:19,120 --> 00:38:20,400
- Mook.
- Yes?

459
00:38:21,600 --> 00:38:23,120
What's your comment on this?

460
00:38:25,520 --> 00:38:27,720
We'll have to adjust our plan to survive.

461
00:38:28,320 --> 00:38:30,480
If we let it go on like this,
we're doomed.

462
00:38:35,920 --> 00:38:38,000
We could plan a tour in Thailand.

463
00:38:38,080 --> 00:38:40,600
Find tourist spots
that are interesting and underrated

464
00:38:40,680 --> 00:38:42,760
and make it a special add-on deal

465
00:38:42,840 --> 00:38:45,200
for customers at The One hotel.

466
00:38:45,280 --> 00:38:46,360
What do you think, Boss?

467
00:38:48,680 --> 00:38:50,120
Sounds interesting.

468
00:38:50,760 --> 00:38:51,760
After all,

469
00:38:51,840 --> 00:38:54,680
special campaigns made for couples
who are soon to be wed

470
00:38:54,760 --> 00:38:56,560
are a hot topic currently.

471
00:38:58,080 --> 00:39:00,360
We can also add on honeymoon packages.

472
00:39:00,440 --> 00:39:03,440
They get married, then go
on their honeymoon. It's all-in-one.

473
00:39:03,520 --> 00:39:04,360
Fabulous!

474
00:39:04,880 --> 00:39:06,680
Start finding a spot.

475
00:39:07,360 --> 00:39:08,640
Can I see?

476
00:39:10,960 --> 00:39:12,320
This is really bad, guys.

477
00:39:16,280 --> 00:39:18,080
The page "High-Class Gossip" just posted.

478
00:39:18,160 --> 00:39:21,680
"Following the news on the relationship
of Mr. Businessman and Ms. Cinderella,

479
00:39:21,760 --> 00:39:24,680
turns out it may have been
just a cover-up story.

480
00:39:24,760 --> 00:39:26,640
We'll have to wait and see

481
00:39:26,720 --> 00:39:30,160
what's real and what's fake."

482
00:39:37,600 --> 00:39:38,560
Mr. Thee.

483
00:39:38,640 --> 00:39:40,360
You've probably seen the news.

484
00:39:41,680 --> 00:39:42,600
Yes.

485
00:39:43,600 --> 00:39:45,120
It must've been that reporter.

486
00:39:45,200 --> 00:39:46,640
She sure is tenacious.

487
00:39:48,160 --> 00:39:49,200
How about this?

488
00:39:49,800 --> 00:39:53,000
Since Mook and Mr. Thee
are already trending,

489
00:39:53,080 --> 00:39:55,400
and everyone's watching,
especially the press,

490
00:39:55,480 --> 00:39:59,240
why don't we just show them
you're actually in love?

491
00:40:00,240 --> 00:40:01,240
No way!

492
00:40:01,960 --> 00:40:03,000
Sure.

493
00:40:04,640 --> 00:40:08,080
Right now, what we need is damage control,

494
00:40:10,080 --> 00:40:12,240
because if there's another scandal,

495
00:40:12,320 --> 00:40:14,320
we'll really be in trouble this time.

496
00:40:18,720 --> 00:40:20,480
Mr. Thee is right.

497
00:40:20,560 --> 00:40:22,200
If another scandal gets out,

498
00:40:22,280 --> 00:40:24,120
there'll be more consequences.

499
00:40:30,560 --> 00:40:32,320
But if you feel uncomfortable,

500
00:40:32,400 --> 00:40:33,920
we'll try to find another way.

501
00:40:42,960 --> 00:40:46,440
I started this trouble,
so I'm responsible for it.

502
00:40:47,520 --> 00:40:50,240
We just have to make it look like

503
00:40:50,320 --> 00:40:52,560
you and Mr. Thee are a real couple.

504
00:40:52,640 --> 00:40:54,560
Not only will we fool the reporters,

505
00:40:54,640 --> 00:40:57,440
we'll make you the faces

506
00:40:57,520 --> 00:41:00,320
of our new campaign for lovers.

507
00:41:00,400 --> 00:41:03,000
We'll kill two birds with one stone.

508
00:41:24,160 --> 00:41:25,440
You've seen the news about Mook?

509
00:41:26,440 --> 00:41:27,360
What news?

510
00:41:33,120 --> 00:41:34,240
FAKE COUPLE! REAL LOVE OR A SHAM

511
00:41:34,320 --> 00:41:37,480
If this is true, I still have a shot.

512
00:41:40,880 --> 00:41:42,120
I mean,

513
00:41:42,640 --> 00:41:44,720
our company still has a shot.

514
00:41:46,920 --> 00:41:48,480
How's this related to our company?

515
00:41:49,640 --> 00:41:52,920
Well, if this news
ruins The One's reputation,

516
00:41:53,440 --> 00:41:55,720
it will be hard for A Round Trip.

517
00:41:57,560 --> 00:42:00,760
So A Round Trip's contract
might get terminated.

518
00:42:02,120 --> 00:42:04,640
And we'll be the only nominee left.

519
00:42:06,920 --> 00:42:09,760
And this might be our last chance.

520
00:42:10,280 --> 00:42:12,360
We can't mess up anymore.

521
00:42:26,280 --> 00:42:28,560
How do I open this? Okay.

522
00:42:31,920 --> 00:42:33,160
Let me drink that.

523
00:42:38,440 --> 00:42:40,200
Were you in a marathon?

524
00:42:40,280 --> 00:42:43,280
You look more wiped out
every time we meet.

525
00:42:44,840 --> 00:42:46,480
If you count the work I'm doing,

526
00:42:46,560 --> 00:42:48,640
it's even worse than a marathon.

527
00:42:50,480 --> 00:42:52,240
Sure sounds like a lot of work.

528
00:42:52,840 --> 00:42:54,240
I don't mind a lot of work.

529
00:42:54,320 --> 00:42:56,160
There's just too many problems.

530
00:42:58,600 --> 00:42:59,920
So,

531
00:43:00,000 --> 00:43:02,880
what's the story about you and Mr. Thee?

532
00:43:04,600 --> 00:43:07,120
It's really nothing.

533
00:43:07,200 --> 00:43:10,040
That day, Mr. Thee said it
just as a cover up,

534
00:43:10,120 --> 00:43:12,520
but that reporter just wouldn't stop.

535
00:43:12,600 --> 00:43:14,680
Guess I'll have to play along for now.

536
00:43:17,040 --> 00:43:19,560
Sure, keep playing along,

537
00:43:19,640 --> 00:43:23,000
but one day, you'll end up
handing out wedding invitations.

538
00:43:23,800 --> 00:43:26,120
Don't be silly. Like I would get married.

539
00:43:29,760 --> 00:43:31,640
Wait, what about Ploy?

540
00:43:31,720 --> 00:43:33,200
Didn't you invite her?

541
00:43:34,600 --> 00:43:35,920
<i>I'm going to tell Ploy</i>

542
00:43:36,000 --> 00:43:38,160
<i>what your true nature is like.</i>

543
00:43:38,240 --> 00:43:39,440
<i>Please go ahead.</i>

544
00:43:39,520 --> 00:43:43,200
<i>Then I'll also tell Ploy</i>
<i>about your true nature.</i>

545
00:43:43,280 --> 00:43:44,720
<i>What do you mean?</i>

546
00:43:44,800 --> 00:43:48,040
<i>I mean that I have video evidence</i>

547
00:43:48,120 --> 00:43:50,880
<i>to show Ploy her best friend's wild side.</i>

548
00:44:00,240 --> 00:44:04,000
<i>Sorry, the number you've dialed</i>
<i>is currently unavailable--</i>

549
00:44:08,080 --> 00:44:11,320
<i>Sorry, the number you've dialed--</i>

550
00:44:15,120 --> 00:44:16,600
Does she know?

551
00:44:18,840 --> 00:44:20,440
I can't get ahold of her.

552
00:44:21,800 --> 00:44:24,320
Do you think… she's okay?

553
00:44:24,400 --> 00:44:27,720
Look, it's normal for newlyweds.

554
00:44:27,800 --> 00:44:30,000
When I got married and moved to Kuk's,

555
00:44:30,080 --> 00:44:32,000
I had to do all kinds of chores.

556
00:44:32,080 --> 00:44:34,200
Next thing I know, I'm already passed out.

557
00:44:34,840 --> 00:44:36,560
Give her some time to settle in.

558
00:44:38,600 --> 00:44:39,680
Right.

559
00:44:43,400 --> 00:44:44,680
Hey,

560
00:44:44,760 --> 00:44:47,720
or is there something
you two haven't told me?

561
00:44:48,720 --> 00:44:50,040
Of course not!

562
00:44:50,120 --> 00:44:51,920
I'm just worried about her.

563
00:44:56,520 --> 00:44:57,960
Aren't you hungry?

564
00:44:58,040 --> 00:44:59,480
Don't go finishing my drink.

565
00:44:59,560 --> 00:45:01,000
Order something.

566
00:45:01,840 --> 00:45:03,080
You almost drank it all.

567
00:45:05,760 --> 00:45:07,280
What should I get?

568
00:45:16,360 --> 00:45:17,760
Where'd you park your car?

569
00:45:18,280 --> 00:45:20,520
I parked it at my office.
I took a motorcycle taxi.

570
00:45:20,600 --> 00:45:23,320
Oh? Then I'll drive you to your office.

571
00:45:23,400 --> 00:45:24,480
Okay.

572
00:45:38,120 --> 00:45:40,600
Aren't you going to introduce me, honey?

573
00:45:42,600 --> 00:45:43,560
What are you doing?

574
00:45:46,840 --> 00:45:49,000
I'm Khim, Mook's best friend.

575
00:45:49,080 --> 00:45:50,960
I've heard about you.

576
00:45:51,040 --> 00:45:52,360
First time seeing you in person.

577
00:45:52,440 --> 00:45:54,520
Nice to meet you, Mr. Thee.

578
00:45:55,120 --> 00:45:57,520
You already told her about us?

579
00:45:58,600 --> 00:46:01,560
Well, of course, everyone knows you now.

580
00:46:02,080 --> 00:46:03,880
We're all over the headlines.

581
00:46:04,680 --> 00:46:06,240
Let go already.

582
00:46:06,320 --> 00:46:08,560
Nice to meet you, Ms. Khim.

583
00:46:08,640 --> 00:46:09,760
Are you two leaving?

584
00:46:10,760 --> 00:46:11,720
Yes,

585
00:46:11,800 --> 00:46:14,120
- I was about to drive her to her office.
- Let's go.

586
00:46:14,200 --> 00:46:17,120
No worries. I'll drive her myself.

587
00:46:17,200 --> 00:46:18,680
Of course.

588
00:46:19,560 --> 00:46:22,640
‪-No.
‪-I'll see you later then. See ya.

589
00:46:22,720 --> 00:46:23,520
- Khim!
- Goodbye.

590
00:46:23,600 --> 00:46:24,920
- Wait, Khim!
- Goodbye.

591
00:46:25,520 --> 00:46:26,760
What are you doing?

592
00:46:26,840 --> 00:46:28,480
Come on. Act the part.

593
00:46:28,560 --> 00:46:29,840
The paparazzi are filming us.

594
00:46:29,920 --> 00:46:30,960
Really?

595
00:46:31,040 --> 00:46:32,000
Where?

596
00:46:32,080 --> 00:46:35,160
Hey, don't be suspicious.

597
00:46:36,640 --> 00:46:38,760
Let's go.

598
00:47:29,840 --> 00:47:32,400
Hey, I'm not a prisoner.

599
00:47:32,480 --> 00:47:34,280
Why are you watching me work?

600
00:47:40,440 --> 00:47:42,320
I'm waiting to drive you home.

601
00:47:43,120 --> 00:47:44,280
Drive me?

602
00:47:44,360 --> 00:47:46,320
Why? You don't have to.
I can go home myself.

603
00:47:51,960 --> 00:47:54,080
What if that paparazzi is still around?

604
00:47:57,120 --> 00:47:57,960
Hey.

605
00:48:00,160 --> 00:48:03,160
Aren't they invading our privacy
a little too much?

606
00:48:07,560 --> 00:48:10,520
I promise I'll sit and wait quietly.

607
00:48:11,600 --> 00:48:12,720
I won't bother you.

608
00:48:13,960 --> 00:48:15,640
And once you're done with work,

609
00:48:16,200 --> 00:48:17,680
I'll drive you home.

610
00:48:18,360 --> 00:48:19,720
Okay? Sound good?

611
00:48:53,720 --> 00:48:54,720
Darn it.

612
00:49:03,440 --> 00:49:04,280
You're back?

613
00:49:05,640 --> 00:49:07,040
Oh, Mom.

614
00:49:08,320 --> 00:49:09,880
Work's so busy lately.

615
00:49:09,960 --> 00:49:11,440
You don't have to wait for me.

616
00:49:12,480 --> 00:49:13,960
I was just waiting with Kongkwan.

617
00:49:14,040 --> 00:49:17,000
She only gave up and went to bed just now.

618
00:49:17,520 --> 00:49:19,480
She kept saying she'd wait for you.

619
00:49:21,840 --> 00:49:23,400
Right. Here, Mook.

620
00:49:23,480 --> 00:49:26,120
The school's sent us a letter
inviting parents to see

621
00:49:26,200 --> 00:49:28,000
the students showcasing their work.

622
00:49:32,600 --> 00:49:35,880
Okay, Mom. I'll try to make it.

623
00:49:37,120 --> 00:49:38,120
That's good.

624
00:49:38,640 --> 00:49:40,720
Kongkwan will be so happy.

625
00:49:41,240 --> 00:49:44,800
She kept telling me
not to forget to tell you.

626
00:49:46,360 --> 00:49:47,200
Okay.

627
00:49:47,280 --> 00:49:50,400
I'm going to bed now. Lock up
and turn off the lights for me, okay?

628
00:49:51,320 --> 00:49:52,960
- Good night, Mom.
- Good night.

629
00:49:53,040 --> 00:49:54,400
Get lots of rest, honey.

630
00:50:21,360 --> 00:50:25,160
Walk pretty. Walk pretty and hold hands.

631
00:50:25,240 --> 00:50:26,080
Mook!

632
00:50:26,160 --> 00:50:28,200
Smile, please. Big smile.

633
00:50:28,280 --> 00:50:30,400
Not a forced smile. A pretty smile.

634
00:50:30,480 --> 00:50:32,320
Can we be done now?

635
00:50:32,400 --> 00:50:34,240
Smile nicely. Look sweeter.

636
00:50:34,320 --> 00:50:35,880
Do we really have to do all this?

637
00:50:35,960 --> 00:50:37,320
Isn't this a bit much?

638
00:50:37,400 --> 00:50:38,720
Hold on, hold on.

639
00:50:40,480 --> 00:50:41,400
Hey.

640
00:50:43,880 --> 00:50:45,040
"A bit much" is good.

641
00:50:45,120 --> 00:50:46,920
We need the photos for promotion.

642
00:50:47,000 --> 00:50:48,640
Smile nicely. Smile.

643
00:50:49,560 --> 00:50:51,320
- Show your teeth.
- Yes.

644
00:50:51,400 --> 00:50:52,280
There.

645
00:50:52,360 --> 00:50:55,320
You look great already. Gosh, I like him.

646
00:50:57,480 --> 00:50:59,280
Okay, this time,

647
00:50:59,360 --> 00:51:01,880
I want some teasing. Make it look cute.

648
00:51:01,960 --> 00:51:03,120
Wait, hey!

649
00:51:03,200 --> 00:51:04,160
What are you doing?

650
00:51:05,840 --> 00:51:07,680
Tell yourself it's for your job.

651
00:51:14,760 --> 00:51:15,920
Wonderful!

652
00:51:17,120 --> 00:51:17,960
Enough.

653
00:51:22,680 --> 00:51:23,520
Let's go.

654
00:51:24,120 --> 00:51:25,200
Smile, Mook.

655
00:51:25,280 --> 00:51:27,400
- Mook, smile!
- Have I not smiled enough?

656
00:51:27,480 --> 00:51:29,880
- Yeah!
- No. Be sweet and look at the camera.

657
00:51:29,960 --> 00:51:31,320
- Quick!
- Yeah.

658
00:51:35,920 --> 00:51:37,080
Too close.

659
00:51:40,280 --> 00:51:42,520
You're really good, Whan. And smart too.

660
00:51:42,600 --> 00:51:45,480
We get to take CSR photos too
while we're here.

661
00:51:46,800 --> 00:51:48,480
It wasn't my idea.

662
00:51:48,560 --> 00:51:50,120
Mr. Thee chose this place.

663
00:51:54,200 --> 00:51:56,720
No wonder he's a successful businessman.

664
00:51:57,320 --> 00:52:00,240
Just imagine, once their photos are posted

665
00:52:00,320 --> 00:52:02,640
with them helping orphans,
showing they love kids,

666
00:52:02,720 --> 00:52:05,160
they'll get so many likes and shares.

667
00:52:07,160 --> 00:52:09,680
Businessmen really do
calculate every move, huh?

668
00:52:10,400 --> 00:52:15,080
Mr. Thee is hot, rich, capable, and smart.

669
00:52:15,160 --> 00:52:17,520
He's so good in every way.

670
00:52:18,920 --> 00:52:19,840
Only thing is,

671
00:52:20,720 --> 00:52:21,880
he never sees me.

672
00:52:26,680 --> 00:52:29,080
- The hell are you doing?
- Looking at you, of course.

673
00:52:29,760 --> 00:52:31,360
I'm looking at you deeply.

674
00:52:31,440 --> 00:52:33,080
I've been for a while now.

675
00:52:33,160 --> 00:52:34,800
You think I can replace him?

676
00:52:36,080 --> 00:52:37,040
You done setting it up?

677
00:52:38,360 --> 00:52:39,520
No.

678
00:52:40,560 --> 00:52:41,800
Just a second.

679
00:52:43,320 --> 00:52:44,280
But

680
00:52:45,240 --> 00:52:46,720
where's Mook and Mr. Thee?

681
00:52:47,600 --> 00:52:49,000
Oh. Oh!

682
00:52:49,080 --> 00:52:52,160
Mr. Thee said he's taking Mook
to see someone he really respects.

683
00:52:52,240 --> 00:52:53,320
They should be back soon.

684
00:52:56,240 --> 00:52:58,640
He even took her to meet the elders?

685
00:53:00,400 --> 00:53:01,920
I guess it's over for me.

686
00:53:06,160 --> 00:53:07,720
Ice cream, please. I need lots of sugar.

687
00:53:17,440 --> 00:53:19,600
PIAMSUK ORPHANAGE

688
00:53:19,680 --> 00:53:21,280
This is Ms. Tassanee.

689
00:53:21,360 --> 00:53:24,720
She's both the teacher, the mother,
and the owner of this place.

690
00:53:26,440 --> 00:53:27,360
Hello.

691
00:53:27,440 --> 00:53:28,840
Hello.

692
00:53:30,520 --> 00:53:33,560
Sai-- Thee, so this is the woman
you told me about.

693
00:53:35,920 --> 00:53:37,280
Make yourself at home.

694
00:53:37,360 --> 00:53:38,800
Thee comes here a lot.

695
00:53:39,320 --> 00:53:40,400
From now on, Ms.…

696
00:53:40,480 --> 00:53:41,920
My name's Mook.

697
00:53:42,000 --> 00:53:44,640
You'll probably come
with him often, Ms. Mook.

698
00:53:48,320 --> 00:53:50,720
You seem familiar with this place.

699
00:53:50,800 --> 00:53:53,120
Do you do CSR activities here a lot?

700
00:53:55,720 --> 00:53:58,960
He's fostered many of the children here.

701
00:53:59,840 --> 00:54:03,600
We're very grateful to him
for helping our disadvantaged children.

702
00:54:04,240 --> 00:54:05,080
We appreciate it.

703
00:54:05,160 --> 00:54:06,200
You're welcome.

704
00:54:07,440 --> 00:54:09,960
I hope you don't mind us
using the place today.

705
00:54:10,840 --> 00:54:12,120
Not at all.

706
00:54:12,200 --> 00:54:13,760
This place is like your home.

707
00:54:13,840 --> 00:54:15,040
Go right ahead.

708
00:54:15,560 --> 00:54:16,440
Okay.

709
00:54:16,520 --> 00:54:17,800
We should be going, then.

710
00:54:17,880 --> 00:54:18,840
The team is waiting.

711
00:54:18,920 --> 00:54:21,200
- Okay.
- Go ahead, Ms. Mook.

712
00:54:24,400 --> 00:54:25,640
Please.

713
00:54:25,720 --> 00:54:27,640
- I'll follow you.
- Okay.

714
00:54:27,720 --> 00:54:29,080
- Let's go.
- Okay.

715
00:54:35,160 --> 00:54:36,200
Here you go.

716
00:54:39,120 --> 00:54:40,800
You seem close to Ms. Tassanee.

717
00:54:40,880 --> 00:54:41,880
Yes.

718
00:54:41,960 --> 00:54:44,880
If it weren't for her,
I wouldn't be where I am today.

719
00:54:50,480 --> 00:54:51,760
I mean,

720
00:54:51,840 --> 00:54:54,120
she's taught me many things,

721
00:54:55,000 --> 00:54:57,560
so I think of her like my second mom.

722
00:54:59,160 --> 00:55:01,320
No wonder you come here a lot.

723
00:55:02,440 --> 00:55:04,480
On our pilot trip, I was wondering

724
00:55:04,560 --> 00:55:07,200
why you chose this place for the program.

725
00:55:07,280 --> 00:55:08,840
Now I understand.

726
00:55:09,560 --> 00:55:10,800
- Yes.
- Mook.

727
00:55:10,880 --> 00:55:11,680
Mook.

728
00:55:12,600 --> 00:55:15,840
Can you feed him? Make it look sweet.

729
00:55:16,560 --> 00:55:17,720
You can feed him now.

730
00:55:18,760 --> 00:55:21,000
- Do it.
- Do it.

731
00:55:21,080 --> 00:55:23,120
- Do it.
- Do it.

732
00:55:23,200 --> 00:55:28,000
- Do it.
- Do it.

733
00:55:41,160 --> 00:55:42,800
- Can we keep handing it out now?
- Go ahead.

734
00:55:47,760 --> 00:55:48,720
<i>Excuse me, miss.</i>

735
00:55:49,240 --> 00:55:50,560
<i>I found this kid</i>

736
00:55:50,640 --> 00:55:52,360
standing there crying outside my house.

737
00:55:52,440 --> 00:55:54,120
I didn't know what to do,

738
00:55:54,200 --> 00:55:57,360
so I brought him here,
in case you can help him.

739
00:55:59,360 --> 00:56:00,840
What happened, sweetie?

740
00:56:01,360 --> 00:56:03,040
Take your time and tell me.

741
00:56:04,760 --> 00:56:06,760
There was a fire at my house.

742
00:56:08,200 --> 00:56:11,040
My little brother was stuck inside.

743
00:56:11,120 --> 00:56:13,240
I couldn't get him out.

744
00:56:13,880 --> 00:56:16,080
Don't blame yourself.

745
00:56:16,160 --> 00:56:17,840
It was an accident.

746
00:56:17,920 --> 00:56:19,560
It's good that you're safe.

747
00:56:22,080 --> 00:56:23,960
- Don't be scared.
- You're okay.

748
00:56:24,040 --> 00:56:25,680
What's your name?

749
00:56:25,760 --> 00:56:27,720
My name is Saifah.

750
00:56:28,680 --> 00:56:30,040
Where are your parents?

751
00:56:30,680 --> 00:56:35,360
Mom said she was going to buy us food.

752
00:56:36,560 --> 00:56:38,640
But… But

753
00:56:38,720 --> 00:56:40,680
she never came back.

754
00:56:41,280 --> 00:56:44,480
Tawan, my brother, he's dead.

755
00:56:51,520 --> 00:56:53,360
It's alright, sweetie.

756
00:56:56,800 --> 00:56:58,080
{\an8}Mook!

757
00:57:00,200 --> 00:57:01,360
{\an8}You've got a nosebleed.

758
00:57:01,440 --> 00:57:03,000
{\an8}- Hold on.
- Wait, Mr. Thee!

759
00:57:03,080 --> 00:57:04,800
{\an8}My friends are making fun of me.

760
00:57:04,880 --> 00:57:07,200
{\an8}They say my mom's going to remarry.

761
00:57:07,280 --> 00:57:11,400
{\an8}I don't want her to remarry.

762
00:57:12,000 --> 00:57:16,560
{\an8}<i>I don't want my mom to be sad.</i>

763
00:57:16,640 --> 00:57:18,160
{\an8}Because I got to see

764
00:57:18,720 --> 00:57:20,440
{\an8}just how much love

765
00:57:20,960 --> 00:57:22,400
{\an8}Mook has for her daughter.

766
00:57:24,200 --> 00:57:26,600
{\an8}I want to protect their feelings.

767
00:57:27,360 --> 00:57:29,280
{\an8}But I hope you haven't forgotten

768
00:57:30,520 --> 00:57:33,000
{\an8}that you already have someone.

769
00:58:26,760 --> 00:58:29,000
{\an8}Subtitle translation by:
Ramil Natnitiwitaya

